Caption: Made with Midjourney


--------------------
**Pulling the plug.** Anthropic=E2=80=99s Claude Fable and Mythos went live=
 for just days before the government suspended them, [citing](https://www.a=
nthropic.com/news/fable-mythos-access) national security. The two groups ar=
e [working](https://techcrunch.com/2026/06/15/the-us-governments-anthropic-=
models-ban-was-never-about-an-ai-jailbreak/) on a solution, but the situati=
on has sent a clear unspoken message =E2=80=94 relying on a single model is=
 becoming increasingly risky.

**Staying prepared. **As the industry evolves, it=E2=80=99s best to assume =
that access to your favorite model could shift without warning. Creating a =
handoff document can help you stay prepared to switch providers without slo=
wing down. Just prompt your AI: "_Write a handoff document I can use to wor=
k successfully with another LLM. Include all stored memories, preferred wor=
kflows, and context you've learned._=E2=80=9D Then feed that document to th=
e next LLM to keep working smoothly.

**Avoiding model lock-in. **Want to go one step further? Consider downloadi=
ng open-weight models, like Google=E2=80=99s [Gemma](https://deepmind.googl=
e/models/gemma/) family, to your own machine. Once downloaded, no lab or go=
vernment can revoke your access. Other benefits: your data stays local, and=
 =3D=3Dyou skip the monthly bills that come with frontier models.=3D=3D

=3D=3D**The bottom line. **=3D=3D=3D=3DThis is one of the first times that =
a government has pulled a live, public AI model=3D=3D =E2=80=94 but it like=
ly won=E2=80=99t be the last. Keeping a handoff document ready or downloadi=
ng open-weight models will make sure you don=E2=80=99t miss a beat as the l=
andscape continues to change.


